Welcome to Future Histories, my name is Jan Gross and it is my great pleasure to welcome

00:05.760 --> 00:08.160
Sören Mao in today's episode.

00:08.160 --> 00:14.720
Sören is a communist philosopher and author of the brilliant book Mute Compulsion, a Marxist

00:14.720 --> 00:20.440
Theory of the Economic Power of Capital, which I enjoyed reading a lot.

00:20.440 --> 00:25.960
And by the way, it's also available in German under the title Stummerzwang, eine Marxistische

00:25.960 --> 00:32.280
Analyse der ökonomischen Macht im Kapitalismus, published by the great Karl Dietz Verlag.

00:32.280 --> 00:34.440
So go and get it.

00:34.440 --> 00:40.860
More recently, an essay by Sören titled Communism as Freedom has been translated from Danish

00:40.860 --> 00:46.280
in multiple languages actually, so it's available in English as well.

00:46.280 --> 00:51.040
Both of these works, the book as well as the essay, are relevant for the conversation you're

00:51.040 --> 00:52.600
about to hear.

00:52.600 --> 00:58.480
Before we start, I'd like to thank Lukas, Fabian and Wilfried for their kind donations

00:58.480 --> 01:04.200
and welcome Markus, Daniel and Jakob as patrons of Future Histories.

01:04.200 --> 01:05.800
Thank you so much.

